1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,771
Four.

2
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,771
But my case is different.

3
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:04,771
I attract bad luck.

4
00:00:05,601 --> 00:00:10,050
Recently, I heard a traffic engineer discuss highway safety.

5
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:16,930
He pointed out that upward of 40,000 persons are killed each year in so-called traffic accidents.

6
00:00:17,121 --> 00:00:22,291
The main point of his talk was that there is no such thing as a true accident.

7
00:00:22,561 --> 00:00:29,331
What we call an accident is the result of human or mechanical failure, or a combination of both.

8
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:35,970
What this traffic expert was saying substantiates what wise men throughout the ages have said.

9
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:38,450
There is a cause for everything.

10
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:41,090
Nothing happens without a cause.

11
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:45,090
There is nothing accidental about the weather outside today.

12
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,891
It is the result of specific causes.

13
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:52,611
And there is no reason to believe that human affairs are an exception.

14
00:00:53,121 --> 00:00:59,251
Yet hardly a day passes that you do not hear someone blame his problems on bad luck.

15
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:05,731
and it's a rare day that you do not hear someone attribute another person's success to good luck.

16
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:10,930
Let me illustrate how people succumb to luck excusitis.

17
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:15,010
I lunched recently with three young junior executives.

18
00:01:15,121 --> 00:01:23,570
The topic of conversation that day was George C., who just yesterday had been picked from among their group for a major promotion.

19
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:26,211
Why did George get the position?

20
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:36,530
These three fellows dug up all sorts of reasons—luck, pull, bootlicking, George's wife and how she flattered the boss—everything but the truth.

21
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:40,371
The facts were that George was simply better qualified.

22
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:42,450
He had been doing a better job.

23
00:01:42,641 --> 00:01:44,050
He was working harder.

24
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,930
He had a more effective personality.

25
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:55,251
I also knew that the senior officers in the company had spent much time considering which one of the four would be promoted.

